	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />I'm no ee expert, but you should do some reading up on how to create a circuit with LEDs in it.  Since the resistance in an LED is so low, it's usually necessary to connect it in series with a resistor.
<br />
<br />And be careful about LED swapping, too.  A long time ago, I swapped the regular red LED in the NES with a green one.  It was connected the right way round, but still fried something in my NES.  <img src="./images/smilies/icon_sad.gif" alt=":-(" title="Sad" />

		

		</td>
	</tr>
